{
  "texts": [
    "ϕ is fixed when the dynamics of CAPs are compared between different lattices.",
    "We use the particle's self-propelling velocity v 0 and the effective radius R as the basic units and set v 0 = R = 1 with the time scale being R/v 0.",
    "Other physical quantities are rescaled by these units, i.e., l p = l p =R, r = r=R, ω 0 = 1= r, and D r = 1= l p.",
    "Noted that the simulation model can be fully described by the two parameters, namely, l p and r.",
    "Echinochloa crus-galli' seed as CAP."
  ]
}